        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 29 at 4:31PM MDT until June 29 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 431 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Briggsdale, or
22 miles northeast of Greeley, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Briggsdale.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and large
hail.</instruction>
